   LineID  PL SL  ----+-*A-1-B--+----2----+----3----+----4----+----5----+----6----+----7-|--+----8 Map and Cross Reference           
0  000001                IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.                                                 |                                  
   000002                PROGRAM-ID.    DICTENC.                                                  |                                  
   000003                AUTHOR.        FRASER.                                                   |                                  
   000004               ******************************************************************        |                                  
   000005               * Program     : DICTENC.CBL                                               |                                  
   000006               * Application : Tiny Pointers lab -- COBOL dictionary encoder             |                                  
   000007               * Type        : Batch COBOL Program                                       |                                  
   000008               * Function    : Dictionary-encode a low-cardinality string COLUMN         |                                  
   000009               *               (the classic column-store compression) using the          |                                  
   000010               *               "load-balancing dereference table" of Tiny Pointers       |                                  
   000011               *               (arXiv:2111.12800, Section 3) as the encode-time          |                                  
   000012               *               string -> code dictionary.                                |                                  
   000013               *                                                                         |                                  
   000014               *   This is the paper's space-efficient DICTIONARY (application #4)       |                                  
   000015               *   doing real database work.  A distinct string is hashed to a           |                                  
   000016               *   BUCKET of B slots and stored in a free slot; the dictionary           |                                  
   000017               *   packs at high load (no 2x safety margin), lossless via a small        |                                  
   000018               *   linear-probe OVERFLOW backup, with a bounded <= B lookup.             |                                  
   000019               *                                                                         |                                  
   000020               *   Pipeline (three flat files, COBOL owns the records):                  |                                  
   000021               *     COLUMN.DAT  -> [encode] -> ENCODED.DAT  + the dictionary            |                                  
   000022               *     COLUMN.DAT  +  ENCODED.DAT -> [decode] -> round-trip check          |                                  
   000023               *                                                                         |                                  
   000024               *   Reports: DENSITY (how tightly the dictionary packs),                  |                                  
   000025               *            HANDLE WIDTH (per-row code vs the full string),              |                                  
   000026               *            and the COLUMN COMPRESSION RATIO.                            |                                  
   000027               ******************************************************************        |                                  
   000028                ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.                                                    |                                  
   000029                INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.                                                    |                                  
   000030                FILE-CONTROL.                                                            |                                  
   000031                    SELECT COLUMN-FILE                                                   |44                                
   000032                        ASSIGN TO 'data/COLUMN.DAT'                                      |                                  
   000033                        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL                                  |                                  
   000034                        FILE STATUS IS COL-STATUS.                                       |88                                
   000035                                                                                         |                                  
   000036                    SELECT ENCODED-FILE                                                  |48                                
   000037                        ASSIGN TO 'data/ENCODED.DAT'                                     |                                  
   000038                        ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL                                  |                                  
   000039                        FILE STATUS IS ENC-STATUS.                                       |90                                
   000040                                                                                         |                                  
   000041                DATA DIVISION.                                                           |                                  
   000042                FILE SECTION.                                                            |                                  
   000043                                                                                         |                                  
   000044                FD  COLUMN-FILE.                                                         |                                  
   000045                01  COL-REC.                                                             |                                  
   000046                    05  COL-STR          PIC X(24).                                      |                                  
   000047                                                                                         |                                  
   000048                FD  ENCODED-FILE.                                                        |                                  
   000049                01  ENC-REC.                                                             |                                  
   000050                    05  EN-CODE          PIC 9(4).                                       |                                  
   000051                                                                                         |                                  
   000052                WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.                                                 |                                  
   000053                                                                                         |                                  
   000054               *--- sizing (D distinct values, N rows; dict load = D/(NBKT*B)) --        |                                  
   000055                01  NBKT                 PIC 9(3) VALUE 35.                              |                                  
   000056                01  BSLOTS               PIC 9(2) VALUE 16.                              |                                  
   000057                01  OVF-CAP              PIC 9(3) VALUE 64.                              |                                  
1PP 5737-L11 IBM COBOL for Linux                     1.2.0      DICTENC   Date 06/13/2026  Time 20:07:55   Page     3               
   LineID  PL SL  ----+-*A-1-B--+----2----+----3----+----4----+----5----+----6----+----7-|--+----8 Map and Cross Reference           
0  000058                01  N-DISTINCT           PIC 9(4) VALUE 500.                             |                                  
   000059                01  N-ROWS               PIC 9(6) VALUE 50000.                           |                                  
   000060                01  STR-BYTES            PIC 9(3) VALUE 24.                              |                                  
   000061                                                                                         |                                  
   000062               *--- the dictionary : NBKT buckets x BSLOTS slots ---------------         |                                  
   000063                01  DICT-STORE.                                                          |                                  
   000064                    05  D-BUCKET OCCURS 35 TIMES.                                        |                                  
   000065                        10  D-SLOT OCCURS 16 TIMES.                                      |                                  
   000066                            15  DS-USED  PIC X.                                          |                                  
   000067                            15  DS-STR   PIC X(24).                                      |                                  
   000068                            15  DS-CODE  PIC 9(4).                                       |                                  
   000069                01  BUCKET-OCC.                                                          |                                  
   000070                    05  B-OCC OCCURS 35 TIMES PIC 9(2).                                  |                                  
   000071                                                                                         |                                  
   000072               *--- the backup table : a small linear-probe overflow region ----         |                                  
   000073                01  OVERFLOW-STORE.                                                      |                                  
   000074                    05  O-CELL OCCURS 64 TIMES.                                          |                                  
   000075                        10  O-USED       PIC X.                                          |                                  
   000076                        10  O-STR        PIC X(24).                                      |                                  
   000077                        10  O-CODE       PIC 9(4).                                       |                                  
   000078                                                                                         |                                  
   000079               *--- code -> string, for DECODE ---------------------------------         |                                  
   000080                01  CODE-TABLE.                                                          |                                  
   000081                    05  CT-STR OCCURS 500 TIMES PIC X(24).                               |                                  
   000082                                                                                         |                                  
   000083               *--- the generator's vocabulary of distinct values --------------         |                                  
   000084                01  VOCAB-TABLE.                                                         |                                  
   000085                    05  VOCAB OCCURS 500 TIMES PIC X(24).                                |                                  
   000086                                                                                         |                                  
   000087               *--- file status ------------------------------------------------         |                                  
   000088                01  COL-STATUS           PIC XX VALUE SPACES.                            |IMP                               
   000089                    88  COL-EOF          VALUE '10'.                                     |                                  
   000090                01  ENC-STATUS           PIC XX VALUE SPACES.                            |IMP                               
   000091                    88  ENC-EOF          VALUE '10'.                                     |                                  
   000092                                                                                         |                                  
   000093               *--- loop / scratch ---------------------------------------------         |                                  
   000094                01  WS-EOF               PIC X VALUE 'N'.                                |                                  
   000095                    88  EOF-YES          VALUE 'Y'.                                      |                                  
   000096                01  WS-I                 PIC 9(9).                                       |                                  
   000097                01  WS-J                 PIC 9(4).                                       |                                  
   000098                01  WS-K                 PIC 9(3).                                       |                                  
   000099                01  WS-S                 PIC 9(6).                                       |                                  
   000100                01  WS-BKT               PIC 9(4).                                       |                                  
   000101                01  WS-OH                PIC 9(6).                                       |                                  
   000102                01  WS-STMP              PIC 9(9).                                       |                                  
   000103                01  WS-HV                PIC 9(18).                                      |                                  
   000104                01  WS-T                 PIC 9(18).                                      |                                  
   000105                01  WS-ORDV              PIC 9(5).                                       |                                  
   000106                01  WS-HSTR              PIC X(24).                                      |                                  
   000107                01  WS-CODE              PIC 9(4).                                       |                                  
   000108                01  WS-FOUND             PIC X VALUE 'N'.                                |                                  
   000109                    88  FOUND-YES        VALUE 'Y'.                                      |                                  
   000110                01  WS-VZ                PIC 9(3).                                       |                                  
   000111                01  WS-VIDX              PIC 9(9).                                       |                                  
   000112                01  WS-NEXT-CODE         PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.                               |                                  
   000113                                                                                         |                                  
   000114               *--- statistics -------------------------------------------------         |                                  
